auth-service

FastAPI gateway in front of phantom-daemon. Ed25519 JWT, Argon2id
passwords, TOTP MFA, RBAC, audit log, authenticated reverse proxy
to the daemon UDS.


v1.1.2 - 2026-05-16
-------------------

  Security maintenance release. Patches the bundled click runtime
  for CVE-2026-7246 (command injection via untrusted shell-quoted
  argument handling on Windows). click is pulled in transitively
  by uvicorn; the bump is surgical (8.3.1 -> 8.3.3) with no source
  or runtime behavior change. Lockfile regenerated via
  `uv pip compile --upgrade-package click`; requirements.in is
  untouched.

  No API, schema, or migration impact.


v1.1.1 - 2026-03-16
-------------------

  Single bump from v1.0.0; everything below shipped as part of this
  version. The work clusters into six logical milestones, written
  between v1.0.0 (Mar 6) and the version bump (Mar 16).

  RBAC, TOTP wizard, MFA hardening

    Introduces admin / superadmin roles enforced by require_auth
    and require_superadmin dependencies. The TOTP enrollment flow
    is rebuilt as a wizard with explicit setup → confirm steps.
    MFA paths are tightened — short-lived MFA token, backup codes
    are one-time and consumed atomically. The /api/* proxy is
    refactored alongside.

  2-step password change with safety net

    Password change splits into verify → change so the new password
    is never sent in the same request as the credential check.
    Setting the same password is rejected outright. A successful
    change revokes every active session for the user, forcing
    re-authentication across all clients.

  Audit log API + per-request audit

    A paginated GET /auth/audit is added (superadmin only) with
    filters and server-side sort that drive the Carbon DataTable on
    the dashboard side directly. Proxy requests are also
    audit-logged, so every daemon API call is attributable to a
    user.

  Error code system + docs

    The error surface is rewritten around an ApiException hierarchy
    plus a stable success_code pattern. Routes are modularised by
    concern (login / session / password / totp / users / audit /
    proxy). The error and env-var contracts get dedicated
    documentation (docs/API_CODES.md, docs/ENV_VARS.md).

  Thread safety + atomic audit pagination

    Audit pagination queries are first wrapped in a single read
    transaction, then collapsed into a single atomic query using
    COUNT(*) OVER() — eliminates the page-size race that could
    show duplicate or missing rows under concurrent inserts.

    The bigger win: SQLite connection management is rewritten as a
    per-request connection opened by an ASGI middleware. Sharing a
    single sqlite3 connection across asyncio workers was a real
    bug; the new model is sharing-free by construction.

  Binary response passthrough + body limit

    The proxy used to assume daemon responses were always JSON.
    Endpoints that return tarballs (backup export) now pass through
    raw, preserving content-type. The default proxy body limit is
    raised from 64 KB to 64 MB so the same backup endpoint can
    also accept large uploads on the inbound side.


v1.0.0 - 2026-03-06
-------------------

  Initial release. The complete authentication layer for
  phantom-daemon — bootstrap, login, MFA, session management, and
  the authenticated reverse proxy that fronts every daemon API
  call.

  * Ed25519 JWT signing and verification, manual implementation
    (no PyJWT dependency).
  * Argon2id password hashing via PyNaCl.
  * RFC 6238 TOTP with hashed one-time backup codes.
  * SQLite WAL-mode persistence for users, sessions, TOTP backup
    codes, and audit log.
  * tools/setup.sh + tools/bootstrap.py: one-shot Ed25519 keypair
    generation, auth.db creation, initial superadmin user with a
    32-char random password (printed once, never persisted in
    plaintext).
  * Authenticated reverse proxy for /api/{path:path} forwarding to
    the daemon over its Unix domain socket, with per-IP
    sliding-window rate limiting on /auth/login.
  * Cross-branch package workflow: builds dist/phantom-auth/ and
    commits the result into dev/daemon:services/auth-service/ as
    github-actions[bot] (see DISTRIBUTION).

  Same-day fixes folded into the release:

    * Ignore chmod failure on Docker-created secrets in CI.
    * Remove duplicate artifact upload from the package workflow.
    * Wire the dev/daemon push end-to-end.
    * Restore /api prefix in the proxy target URL (regression
      caught immediately after the initial commit).
